{"DOVE":[{"def":"A pigeon of the genus Columba and various related genera.","pos":""},{"def":"A small house or box, raised to a considerable height above the ground, and having compartments, in which domestic pigeons breed; a dove house.","pos":""}],"DOVE PLANT":[{"def":"A Central American orchid (Peristeria elata), having a flower stem five or six feet high, with numerous globose white fragrant flowers.","pos":""}],"DOVE-EYED":[{"def":"Having eyes like a dove; meekeyed; as, dove-eyed Peace.","pos":""}],"DOVEKIE":[{"def":"A guillemot (Uria grylle), of the arctic regions.","pos":""}],"DOVELET":[{"def":"A young or small dove.","pos":""}],"DOVELIKE":[{"def":"Mild as a dove; gentle; pure and lovable.","pos":""}],"DOVER'S POWDER":[{"def":"A powder of ipecac and opium, compounded, in the United States, with sugar of milk, but in England (as formerly in the United States) with sulphate of potash, and in France (as in Dr.","pos":""}],"DOVESHIP":[{"def":"The possession of dovelike qualities, harmlessness and innocence.","pos":""}],"DOVETAIL":[{"def":"A flaring tenon, or tongue (shaped like a bird's tail spread), and a mortise, or socket, into which it fits tightly, making an interlocking joint between two pieces which resists pulling a part in all directions except one.","pos":""}],"DOVISH":[{"def":"Like a dove; harmless; innocent.","pos":""}]}